The paper proposes a novel indexing scheme for solving the problem of approximate k-nearest neighbor queries in high-dimensional databases. This problem is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including information retrieval (IR), databases (DB), computer vision (CV), data structures (DS), and machine learning (LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CV, cs.DS, and cs.LG, in that order.
